 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Observational Seismologist ENSCO, Inc. 41 reviews Melbourne, FL 32940 ENSCO, Inc. 41 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Job Description 
 ENSCO, Inc. is seeking observational seismologist to work closely with a team of scientists and analysts focusing on the interpretation/analysis of waveform data from local and regional distances. The work is mission critical and involves solving real-world problems. A solid understanding of observational seismology is required. Develop innovative analysis techniques/tools to meet customer objectives. Work with software engineering team to develop/validate analysis toolsets. The applicant must have competence in algorithm development, data analysis and digital signal processing techniques, including time domain correlation, array beamforming, and spectral analysis. Responsible for the technical preparation of scientific reports. Publication in referred scientific journals and at scientific conferences is encouraged. 
 Qualifications Required (Skills) 
 BS is Geophysics with emphasis in seismology, with minimum 5 years related experience. 
Experience collecting, processing, and analyzing local/regional seismic data (phase identification, velocity, and attenuation models), including an understanding of earthquake magnitude scales and their derivation. 
Demonstrated digital signal processing expertise including, but not limited to signal detection algorithms and spectral analysis. 
Demonstrated ability to organize, evaluate, and validate geophysical sensor metadata, including seismic instrument responses. 
Demonstrated scientific programming skills such as UNIX/Linux OS, Java/C/Fortran/Python/Matlab scientific programming and scripting languages (e.g., Perl, R, C-Shell), database queries (e.g., SQL), seismic code (e.g., SAC, SEISAN, Obspy), and mapping software (e.g., GMT, ArcView). 
Ability to work in a team environment and as a self-starter. 
Excellent oral and written communication skills. 
Technical skills to understand and analyze problems, define potential solutions, and conduct in-depth technical analysis, assessments, and trades, and assist in explaining results of technical studies in team meetings, public forums such as conferences, and to non-expert customers. 
Able to assimilate complex scientific data from disparate sources and analyze results. 
Experience with Microsoft Office, including scientific applications using Excel, Word, and PowerPoint. 
Established record of geophysical scientific research and publication in referred journals required. 
Experience preparing technical proposals. 
Ability to obtain a Top Secret Sensitive Compartmented Information security clearance, for which you must be a U.S. Citizen. If you do not meet this requirement, you will not be considered. 
 Qualifications Desired 
 PhD degree in Geophysics or a related discipline, or equivalent. 
Familiar with regional seismic discrimination methods and techniques. 
Familiarity with CSS3.0 database schema. 
Experience with regional seismic network operations. 
Active US security clearance. 
